    <sec id="Sec23">
      <title>Scalp Laplacian</title>
      <p id="Par67">(Hjorth <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR22">1975</xref>) proposed the use of a mathematical procedure for an estimation of brain generators of scalp EEG potentials. The procedure tried to estimate the orthogonal current through the skull entering (sink) or exiting (source) the scalp at each electrode site, so the result was originally called “orthogonal source derivation”. Scalp/Surface Laplacian (SL) is a discretization of the planar Laplacian operator, i.e. the difference between the potential at each electrode and the averaged potential of its nearest four neighbors.</p>
      <p id="Par68">In practice, SL can be estimated by a simple subtraction of a channel <inline-formula id="IEq39"><alternatives><tex-math id="M107">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
